      "name": "CISCO_PSU_FAULT",
      "code": 100041,
      "description": "Generated when a Cisco power supply unit reports a non-normal state. Triggered by ciscoEnvMonSupplyState (CISCO-ENVMON-MIB).\n\nState codes:\n   1 = normal\n   2 = warning\n   3 = critical\n   4 = shutdown\n   5 = notPresent\n   6 = notFunctioning\n\nTo suppress alarms on absent/redundant slots (state 5), set node custom attribute:\n   Template.CiscoPerformance.SuppressNotPresent = Yes",
      "severity": 3,
      "flags": 1,
      "message": "PSU %<instanceName>: state %<currentValue> (1=normal, 2=warning, 3=critical, 4=shutdown, 5=notPresent, 6=notFunctioning)",
