      "id": 1404,
      "guid": "face9d7a-1c4c-49a0-ad4d-c0e3996bb03b",
      "name": "Cisco performance",
      "comments": "Template to monitor health and performance of Cisco SNMP devices.\n\nAuto-applies to nodes whose sysObjectID is under the Cisco enterprise OID (1.3.6.1.4.1.9.1.*).\n\nDCIs collected:\n- Memory pool usage % (CISCO-MEMORY-POOL-MIB)\n- CPU 1-minute average usage % (CISCO-PROCESS-MIB)\n- Running vs startup configuration synchronization (CISCO-CONFIG-MAN-MIB)\n- Power supply, fan, temperature value and status, and voltage status (CISCO-ENVMON-MIB)\n\nFaults raise dedicated events: CISCO_CONFIG_NOT_SAVED, CISCO_PSU_FAULT, CISCO_FAN_FAULT, CISCO_TEMPERATURE_FAULT, CISCO_VOLTAGE_FAULT. A single EPP rule converts all of them into alarms; alarm key follows the standard DC_THRESHOLD_* pattern so the default rearm rule terminates them automatically when state returns to normal.\n\nBy default, environmental components in state notPresent (5) raise alarms - useful when redundant components are expected to always be installed. To suppress those alarms on chassis with declared-but-empty slots, set node custom attribute `Template.CiscoPerformance.SuppressNotPresent` to value `Yes`.",
      "exclusionGroup": "",
      "path": [
        "SNMP",
        "Routers & Switches"
      ],
      "dataCollection": {
        "dcis": [
          {
            "id": 1136,
